            "answer_text": "Nobody needs to copy recommended candidates story because it is a personality test. Try to understand logic behind the test.The picture story test as it is commonly called is termed as (PPDT) \u201cPicture perception and description test\u201d during screening. The same test little modified is called (TAT) \u201cthematic apperception test\u201d during psychology day. Why? There is a difference between perception & apperception. In simple worlds perception is how you see the world and apperception is how you make meaning of people's expectations, motives, behaviours around you. So, TAT is an interpersonal test. The cards are scientifically prepared to prompt your behaviour and feeling toward others- Picture of boy and girl (same age)- your views towards opposite gender.Picture of boy and elderly woman/man- your views towards elders (mostly your parents)Picture of lonely person standing near window or on bridge or near a tree (lonely setting)- very important in finding out if the person finds positivity or has suicidal/depressed feelings.Picture of many boys/girls- your views towards your friends or at work place or social gathering.Picture of accident, death- your views on bad life affecting event.Now, how the stories are scored is a controversial, difficult and unknown topic. It totally depends on the psychologist. But, if done a research on net, one can find one of the ways for scoring is \u201cSocial Cognition & Object Relation Scale- General rating\u201d (SCORS-G). In this the stories are scored on 8 parameters (not necessary all parameters are included in one story)- Complexity of representation of people (insight into self and others)- In psychology complexity means when you take not only your own view but others view also in consideration.Affect-tone of relationship schema- affect-tone are of two types negative and positive. How is relation with other negative or positive? Is it one-sided or mutual.Emotional investment in relationship- how is the relationship with others at emotional level.Emotional investment in values and moral standards- does the character have values and moral standards.understanding of social causality- this is important and complex topic. Have to Google yourself to understand.Experience and management of aggressive impulse- shows aggression or puts his point firmly in proper non-aggressive manner.self-esteemIdentity and coherence of self- long term goals and ambitions.",
