                "href": "/profile/Deepak-Parwani-6"
            },
            "answer_text": "Do not try and copy stories for TAT. Keep it your own. Else it would not match with your responses in WAT, SRT, SD. They would be contrasting. Some basics for TAT- write small sentences. Dont try and use flowery words, simple english would do. Keep your handwriting readable. Write what humans can easily do, either alone or with the help of others. No superman, batman stuff please. The problem statement in your story may not always be a murder, floods. Earthquake etc, electricity not being there on an exam night is also a problem on which you can write a good story. Every story need not finish with rewards/awards. Sometimes you solve problems as a part of your daily routine. The length of the story doesnt matter, its the content which does. All the best. ",
